Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with cut elimination in propositional logic deep inference proofs. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also likely as the paper mentions the quasipolynomial time complexity of the cut elimination procedure. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possibility as the paper introduces a new computational trace of deep-inference proofs called atomic flows. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possibility as the paper deals with logical inference, which is a fundamental component of AI. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possibility as the paper deals with the structure of proofs in propositional logic, which is relevant to programming language semantics.
